caption.p: Change point plots: ( a) influenza A and human Metapneumovirus exhibited their highest mean counts in the 2009–2010 season; ( b) influenza B exhibited its highest mean count in the 2012–2013 season; ( c) respiratory syncytial virus (RSV) and rhinovirus exhibited their highest mean counts in the 2012–2013 season; and ( d) enterovirus (EV) exhibited its highest mean count in 2011.
